basics.name: Gellie Cabuyadao
basics.label: Student
basics.summary: I am studying for a B.B.A in Management Information Systems at the Shidler's College of Business, University of Hawai'i at Manoa. I enlisted in the United States Navy and was selected for the Seaman To Admiral (STA-21) commissioning program FY22. I expect to graduate and commission as a Naval Officer in Spring, 2025.

work.position: Information Systems Technician Second Class Petty Officer
work.summary: NCTSS II MGR Operator and Systems Administrator
highlights: Maintain, update, and operate Navy's global satellite telecommunications systems
Drive, design and build computers, local and wide area networks in the fleet

awards.title: Navy and Marine Corps Achievement Medal
awards.summary: Awarded by her coordination in nine indoctrination courses and timely delivery of 164 Welcome Aboard and Assignment messages. Ensured 100 percent compliance for 13 personnel as cybersecurity workforce coordinator.

awards.title: Navy and Marine Corps Achievement - Medal Gold Star In Lieu of Second Award
awards.summary: Awarded by her assured troubleshooting connectivity of eight laptops during a four week virtual shore tactical training for 28 trainees.

awards.title: Navy and Marine Corps Achievement - Medal Gold Star In Lieu of Third Award
awards.summary: Awarded by her superior performance in leading five sailors, 11 indoctrination courses, 136 Welcome Aboard Messages.
